Commentary Text: Cummins to Dhawan, out Bowled!! No third ton for Dhawan. Cummins spoils the party and look at the sight of that off-stump which has been uprooted. Delhi in a spot of bother here. Shortened his length and gets it to nibble away a fraction at the last moment, Dhawan missed the line totally, playing it away from his body and it beats the outside edge to kiss the stumps. Cummins leaps in delight and KKR have removed both the openers early. Dhawan b Cummins 6(6) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: Cummins to Rahane, out Lbw!! Anddd that's a dream start for KKR and Cummins. This is what the speedster can do with the new ball and this is what his team want from him. Fullish with a hint of inward shape after pitching. Rahane's feet went nowhere, he didn't bother to cover for the movement and ended up missing it altogether. Struck low on the pad in front of middle and that's one of the plumbest LBW's you'll ever see. Simple call for the umpire Pashchim Pathak and Rahane just turns back and walks away without even pondering about the review. Golden duck on his comeback game for Jinks, gee! Rahane lbw b Cummins 0(1)
